
    UMZIMKHULU mayor Mphuthumi Mpabanga said he was certain the continuous police operations in the area will rid the surrounding villages of rotten potatoes.Mpabanga’s remarks follow the arrest of two men aged 43 and 33 on Monday who are suspected of manufacturing whoonga near the Umzimkhulu border.The men were allegedly found in possession of several substances believed to be whoonga ingredients. According to sources, cops were alerted by residents who led them to a two-roomed house where the suspects were allegedly caught manufacturing the drug.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsvFct-tkJpacSPNUj-dLitV9d6seV2QmWs3OsQg_1G3bJaswuMTM-idb3iRHHPlxgekH4kRbA6vPJVviAwSwUdaRdM6Nz5DVy1nIIUN6laNxDgmUlW8hwLrSsdSqGAthtDn-ZYuL_kbOTA7OxspxyoPb3wNE-P_snp6ew3WSDnKW5aaCA4ij8PgZqT3hIPzF0ZwxGygn3yMhaWzgRzj8Idnxm2C8NCfohlNT3rVnzdalk9Awg_ro3UgPw3K64_nrkFyciHJUH8aXfai35VX1rE5KPfkmbk\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzPKavAVEkS4DEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
